reviewText: You have seen several movies where one wonders innocently into testing grounds. Remember "No Time for Sergeants?"  Alternatively "The Power" with George Hamilton?Well Blix (Mickey Rooney) comes upon a house where the occupants are real dummies. Not realizing the significance, he proceeds to consume a peanut butter sandwich. The unthinkable happens. But what is this? Blix is still alive and now takes on a glowing complexion. A quasi love interest appears in the hospital with (Elaine Davis). Then come FBI and spies. Eventually there is déjà vu.There must be something here as it is a story by Blake Edwards.
Title: N/A

reviewText: For some reason, I had pleasant memories of watching this film on tv as a child in the early 60s and bought it the day it was issued on BR.I should have let the memory be.Bad slapstick, flat writing and a painfully hammy Mickey Rooney provided nary a chuckle in the seemingly interminable time it took to watch this relatively short film. Maybe it's just not that easy to get laughs out of nuclear accidents and boneheaded writing.Archival films of civil defense preparedness offer more entertainment value than sitting through this snoozer.
summary: Memory does not serve...this is a flaccid, flat unfunny slog...
Title: N/A

reviewText: The Atomic Kid is a cute movie, but not one that will ever wear out in your Blu-Ray player from constant use. Every couple of years or so you might want to see it again...or not.  Mickey Rooney has an enormously engaging personality but the plot, especially to modern audiences who are more nuclear savvy, is unworthy of his great talent.
summary: Cute Movie, Not Cecil B. DeMille

reviewText: As announced on "HTF", The Atomic Kid (1954), will be released on 03-26-2013, and published by Olive Films, with an SRP of $19.99. This Sci-Fi/Comedy, stars Mickey Rooney and Robert Strauss, as survivors of an atomic bomb test and it's aftermath. Radioactive 1950's fun ensues ala "Martin & Lewis" (w/o the singing).  I've waited since 1995 for this film...and I can't wait for Amazon to make pre-ordering available(better sooner than later) please !!!Have fun in 2013 :) :) :)JWC II
summary: Mickey Rooney Does Jerry Lewis And Survives An Atomic Bomb ?

reviewText: I saw this film in my youth.  It was one few with Mickey Rooney in it that I liked.  It also features Robert Strauss, whom I first saw in the Jerry Lewis / Dean Martin film "Jumping Jacks."  This particular film blends science fiction, cold war intrigue, and sheer comedy.  It's far from a classic but charming and enjoyable nevertheless.  I' glad it was finally released on DVD.
